olive oil
1 packet orecchiette
1 leek
1 tomato
2 clove garlic
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 bag parsley
½ bottle cream
½ tin Crushed & Sieved Tomatoes
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Bring a large saucepan of salted water to the boil. Cook orecchiette in boiling water until 'al dente', 8 minutes.
• Drain, reserving some pasta water (1/4 cup for 2 people / 1/2 cup for 4 people), then return orecchiette to the saucepan.
• Meanwhile, thinly slice leek. Finely chop tomato, garlic and mild chorizo.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook mild chorizo, tossing, until golden, 4-5 minutes.
• Transfer chorizo to a plate, leaving any residual oil in the pan.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat. Cook leek and tomato, until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and garlic & herb seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Return chorizo to the pan, then add cream (see ingredients), crushed & sieved tomatoes (see ingredients), cooked orecchiette and reserved pasta water.
• Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, 2 minute. Season to taste.

• Divide creamy tomato and chorizo orecchiette between bowls.
• Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese. Tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch and sprinkle over the cheese and herbs!